@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
    var lastUpdated = DateTime.UtcNow.ToString("yyyy-MM-dd");
}

<div class="container py-5">
    <h1 class="mb-3">@ViewData["Title"]</h1>
    <p class="text-muted small">Last updated: @lastUpdated</p>

    <p>This Privacy Policy describes how AmosWRN ("we", "our", "us") collects, uses, and shares information when you use our website and weather services.</p>

    <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
    <h5>Personal information you provide</h5>
    <p>Examples: name, email address, account information, and other information you choose to provide when you sign up or contact us.</p>

    <h5>Automatically collected data</h5>
    <p>Examples: usage data, IP address, device and browser information, cookies, and analytic data used to improve our services.</p>

    <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>To provide and maintain the Service, including providing forecasts and alerts.</li>
        <li>To improve and personalize the Service, analyze usage, and diagnose problems.</li>
        <li>To communicate with you (updates, support, transactional messages).</li>
        <li>To comply with legal obligations and protect our rights.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. Legal Bases for Processing (if applicable)</h2>
    <p>Where required (for example, under the GDPR), we process personal data based on consent, performance of a contract, legitimate interests, or legal obligations.</p>

    <h2>4. Cookies and Similar Technologies</h2>
    <p>We use cookies and similar technologies to recognize you, remember preferences, and collect analytics. You can control cookie settings through your browser or via any provided preference tools.</p>

    <h2>5. Third-Party Services</h2>
    <p>We may share data with service providers (e.g., hosting, analytics, email delivery). Third parties have their own privacy practices; please review their policies.</p>

    <h2>6. Data Security</h2>
    <p>We implement reasonable administrative, technical, and physical safeguards to protect personal data. However, no internet transmission is completely secure; we cannot guarantee absolute security.</p>

    <h2>7. Data Retention</h2>
    <p>We retain personal data only as long as necessary to provide the Service, for legal compliance, and to resolve disputes. When no longer needed, data is securely deleted or anonymized.</p>

    <h2>8. Your Rights</h2>
    <p>Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have rights including access, correction, deletion, restriction, portability, and objection to processing. To exercise rights, contact us at the address below.</p>

    <h2>9. Children's Privacy</h2>
    <p>Our Service is not intended for children under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal data from children without parental consent.</p>

    <h2>10. International Transfers</h2>
    <p>Data may be processed in countries other than your country of residence. We take steps to ensure an adequate level of protection when transferring data.</p>

    <h2>11. Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>We may update this policy from time to time. We will post the revised date and, where appropriate, notify users of significant changes.</p>

    <h2>12. Contact Us</h2>
    <p>If you have questions, request to exercise your rights, or want more information about our privacy practices, contact:</p>
    <address>
        AmosWRN Support<br />
        Email: <a href="mailto:privacy@amoswrn.example">privacy@amoswrn.example</a>
    </address>

    <hr />
    <p class="text-muted small">This privacy notice is provided for informational purposes and does not constitute legal advice. For compliance with specific laws (GDPR, CCPA), consult legal counsel to tailor this policy to your jurisdiction and data practices.</p>
</div>
